        Official Singles Chart on 31/3/2017

        31 March 2017 - 6 April 2017

        The Official UK Singles Chart reflects the UKs biggest songs of the week, based on audio and video streams, downloads, CDs and vinyl, compiled by the Official Charts Company. The UK Top 40 is broadcast on BBC Radio 1 and MTV, the Top 100 is published exclusively on OfficialCharts.com. View the biggest songs of 2024 so far.

        "Shape of You" by Ed Sheeran remains at number 1 on the Official UK Singles Chart for a 12th straight week. The song has already reached number one in more than 30 countries "Galway Girl", also by Ed Sheeran, remains at number 2.

        "Passionfruit" by Drake rises from number 4 to number 3 this week. The song is the second single off Drake's new playlist, "More Life" (also known as More Life: A Playlist by October Firm), which was released on March 18, 2017 by Young Money Entertainment and Cash Money Records.

        "Symphony" by Clean Bandit featuring Zara Larsson rises two places to number 4 this week.

        "Still Got Time" by Zayn featuring PartyNextDoor debuts on the chart at number 24. It's the first single from Malik's upcoming second studio album. The song was produced by Murda Beatz ("No Frauds" by Nicki Minaj featuring Drake and Lil' Wayne) and Frank Dukes ("Fake Love").

        Piran

        My thoughts & observations on the UK charts as always
        - Shape Of You by Ed Sheeran earns a 12th consecutive week at #1 on the Official Charts. As I said back on Mondays update article, as much as I think its a decent song, its also becoming both overrated & overplayed. Its got the point where the magnitude of its appeal is becoming annoying; there are far better tracks from Eds album that deserve this level of success.
        - There are still only two songs in the chart right now that could challenge for #1 in the next week or two; Galway Girl by Ed Sheeran (which has good sales & good streaming) or Symphony by Clean Bandit ft Zara Larsson (which has excellent sales & decent streaming). I like both of these way more than Shape Of You, so Id be happy with either taking #1 next.
        - Chained To The Rhythm by Katy Perry ft Skip Marley leads the UK radio airplay chart for a fourth consecutive week.
        - Drake earns his 10th Top 10 hit in the UK as Blem climbs 14-10. Of all of the songs on More Life, I dont understand why this has been one of the most successful so far. The tropical beat is decent but has become so generic over these past few months, Drakes vocals sound dreary & boring like on most of the playlist & if you Google the word Blem, youll understand another reason why I lose respect for this song.
        - There was only one new arrival in the Top 40 this week; Still Got Time by ZAYN ft PARTYNEXTDOOR enters at #24, becoming the formers 23rd UK Top 40 hit (18 with 1D & 5 as a solo artist). I can see why this song wasnt on Zayns Mind Of Mine album, because it strays away from the R&B scene & sees him move back slightly into pop with a catchy & groovy dancehall anthem. It wouldve been nice to have had more interesting verses from PARTYNEXTDOOR though. Overall, Still Got Time is good, but not great.
        - Although this is mostly due to the continued losses for the Ed Sheeran & Drake albums tracks, the biggest climbers in the Top 40 this week were: Paris by The Chainsmokers (38-29), Green Light (40-26, new peak), Scared To Be Lonely by Martin Garrix & Dua Lipa (30-20) & Thats What I Like by Bruno Mars (25-15, new peak) & Issues by Julia Michaels (28-13, new peak). I would rate these songs: 8/10, 9/10, 7/10, 9/10 & 6/10 respectively, so a really positive week in terms of climbers.
        - On the albums chart, its four weeks at #1 for by Ed Sheeran. The rest of the Top 5 is: Wonderland by Take That (debuts at #2), More Life by Drake (2-3), Human by RagnBone Man (5-4) & 100 by Vera Lynn (3-5). Wonderland is Take Thats 11th Top 10 album!
        - For next Friday, new Top 40 arrivals could include: Heatstroke by Calvin Harris ft Young Thug, Pharrell Williams & Ariana Grande, Waterfall by Stargate ft P!NK & Sia, No Promises by Cheat Codes ft Demi Lovato, Humble by Kendrick Lamar & more.
        - Overall, nothing too interesting happened this week, but Im ecstatic to see It Aint Me rebound to its peak (19-7). Thanks for reading everyone & have a nice weekend. :)
